╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 2.1: Line Selection                   ║
║  Category: Selection             Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  x     Select the current line (repeat to extend to more lines)
  X     Extend selection to full line bounds
  d     Delete the selection

MNEMONIC: x = line (think "x marks the whole line")

NOTE: In Helix, x selects a line. In Vim, x deletes a character.
      This is one of the biggest differences!

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Delete all lines that contain the word "REMOVE".
  Keep all other lines exactly as they are.

  Strategy:
  1. Move to a line containing REMOVE
  2. Press x to select the entire line
  3. Press d to delete it

  For consecutive REMOVE lines, press x multiple times to
  extend the selection across all of them, then d once.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Keep this line.
REMOVE this line.
Keep this one too.
REMOVE this as well.
REMOVE and this.
This stays.
REMOVE goodbye.
The end stays.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

Keep this line.
Keep this one too.
This stays.
The end stays.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Move to "REMOVE this line." and press x then d.
  Hint 2: For the two consecutive REMOVE lines, press x twice
          to select both, then d to delete them together.
  Hint 3: If you accidentally select the wrong line, press ;
          to collapse the selection back to a cursor.
